/17/squarespace-makes-everything-easy-except-your-crazy-life</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5134cbefe4b0c6fb04df8065:5134cbefe4b0c6fb04df8086:5d07af30c2c5b00001d87c3e</guid><description><![CDATA[Shots]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class=""><strong>In a series of comedic spots, the site-building service gives us a glimpse of the wild and wacky worlds of some of its users.</strong></p><p class="">It's nice when a company can do something really, really well and doesn't pretend to do more than that. As these new spots for site-building service Squarespace go to show, they might be great at helping you create a great-looking web presence easily, but they're not there to sort out your relationship regrets/assistant animosity/doggie dramas.</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><p class=""><a href="https://shots.net/news/view/squarespace-makes-everything-easy-except-your-crazy-life" target="_blank">Read more</a>. </p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Cold feet and hot styles for dogs get their own quirky Squarespace websites</title><dc:creator>Ahrim Nam</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2019 15:17:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://adage.com/creativity/work/squarespace-squarespace-not-squarespace/2175651</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5134cbefe4b0c6fb04df8065:5134cbefe4b0c6fb04df8086:5d07aec7ba7f6100014762c1</guid><description><![CDATA[Ad Age]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class=""><strong>The brand's latest campaign shows how the it can solve most—but not all—of its users problems.<br><br></strong></p><p class=""><br>These days, websites are like lemonade stands in the 1950s. Having one doesn’t guarantee getting noticed, but it’s impossible without one.</p><p class="">Squarespace has made a splash in the last few years with big Super Bowl and Super-Bowl adjacent spots featuring celebrity personalities. Now the website-building platform has unveiled a more low-key—though no less absurdist—campaign.<br></p><p data-rte-preserve-